[5] Cholera - South Sudan
Date: Fri 5 Sep 2014
Source: IFRC [edited]
http://www.ifrc.org/en/news-and-media/news-stories/africa/south-sudan/tackling-cholera-outbreaks-in-south-sudan-66993/


South Sudan is currently battling a cholera outbreak. Since mid-May 2014, cholera outbreaks or alerts have been reported in 7 of South Sudan's 10 states with, as of mid-August 2014, 5859 reported cases and 127 deaths. The South Sudan Red Cross has mobilized and trained hundreds of volunteers to spread messages about cholera prevention through home visits and through the use of radio and mobile cinema.

[Byline: Chiran Livera and Marial Mayom]

