******
[7] Cholera - India (Odisha State)
Date: Mon 8 Sep 2014
Source: Odisha Sun Times [edited]
http://odishasuntimes.com/85153/cholera-scare-odishas-narla-block-lab-tests-confirm-presence-bacteria/


Laboratory tests of rectal swabs collected from patients in Narla block of Odisha's Kalahandi district have confirmed the presence of deadly _Vibrio cholerae_ in them, sources said. Three persons have succumbed to cholera in the interior areas of Narla in the last 15 days after the disease spread in the block, reports said. An elderly woman and 2 children are among the dead, reports added.

The district administration had sent rectal swabs of some patients to Bhubaneswar for laboratory tests after the condition of around 120 persons afflicted with gastroenteritis turned serious between 20 Aug 2014 and 5 Sep 2014, reports said.

